<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Smith, Robert (1972). <i>A Social History of the Bicycle, its Early Life and Times in America</i>. American Heritage Press.</li>
<li id="cite_note-fromhighway-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-fromhighway_11-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://md1.csa.com/partners/viewrecord.php?requester=gs&amp;collection=ENV&amp;recid=5182080&amp;q=car+culture&amp;uid=789848837&amp;setcookie=yes" class="external text" title="http://md1.csa.com/partners/viewrecord.php?requester=gs&amp;collection=ENV&amp;recid=5182080&amp;q=car+culture&amp;uid=789848837&amp;setcookie=yes" rel="nofollow">From Highway to Superhighway: The Sustainability, Symbolism and Situated Practices of Car Culture</a> Graves-Brown. Social Analysis. Vol. 41, pp. 64-75. 1997.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://politics.guardian.co.uk/columnist/story/0,9321,1671055,00.html" class="external text" title="http://politics.guardian.co.uk/columnist/story/0,9321,1671055,00.html" rel="nofollow">George Monbiot, The Guardian, Tuesday December 20, 2005</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Directly from: <a href="http://www.benbest.com/lifeext/causes.html" class="external free" title="http://www.benbest.com/lifeext/causes.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.benbest.com/lifeext/causes.html</a> See <i>Accident as a Cause of Death</i><br />
Derived from: National Vital Statistics Report, Volume 50, Number 15 (September 2002)</li>
<li id="cite_note-Shoup-14">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Shoup_14-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Shoup_14-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=K1qYHgAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22the+high+cost+of+free+parking%22&amp;ei=G56TR8SwMIKg7gLz-sGtBw&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=K1qYHgAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22the+high+cost+of+free+parking%22&amp;ei=G56TR8SwMIKg7gLz-sGtBw&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1" rel="nofollow">The High Cost of Free Parking</a></i> by Donald C. Shoup</li>
<li id="cite_note-Vuchic-15">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Vuchic_15-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Vuchic_15-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Vuchic_15-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Vuchic_15-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> Graph based on data from <i>Transportation for Livable Cities</i> By Vukan R. Vuchic page. 76. 1999. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0882851616" class="internal">ISBN 0882851616</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> MacKenzie, J.J., R.C. Dower, and D.D.T. Chen. 1992. <i>[<a href="http://www.wristore.com/goinratwhati.html" class="external free" title="http://www.wristore.com/goinratwhati.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.wristore.com/goinratwhati.html</a> The</i> Going Rate: What It Really Costs to Drive]<i>. Washington, DC: World Resources Institute.</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.its.ucdavis.edu/people/faculty/delucchi" class="external free" title="http://www.its.ucdavis.edu/people/faculty/delucchi" rel="nofollow">http://www.its.ucdavis.edu/people/faculty/delucchi</a></li>
